=\r\nep for which maybe calming the external mind and emotions, then one can eve=\r\nntually discover a clear and spontaneous and sure guidance, for it uses not=\r\n the mental reason, or is not driven by emotions vacillations at all, but i=\r\ns connected in some peculiar way to the Divine. This spontenity is prized. =\r\nThen one may say, as one goes deeper and this state of living from within b=\r\necomes more settled, that one is but a mere instrument in the flow of the D=\r\nivine Rhythm. Before that, we are all subject to out free wills and repercu=\r\nssions thereof.&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_1454937201388_319=\r\n94&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_145493720138=\r\n8_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Often by a generic use of the term spontaneity, or inn=\r\ner voice, we mean a normal reaction that we have been inculcating to situat=\r\nions and which has become so ingrained that we do not even think before we =\r\nact into it. For example an aggressive person whose first reaction to every=\r\n situaiton is an act of aggression, will always *spontaneously* behave that=\r\n way whenever a difficult life situation comes up. Or an escapist who has b=\r\neen escaping all his life will first automatically think of escaping from a=\r\n difficult situation because thath is what his conditioned response is. &nb=\r\nsp;That too is spontaneous, but spiritually useless. If anything it reinfor=\r\nces the tendencies that we live by. The spiritual spontaneity arises as one=\r\n goes deeper within, which of course is not easy and needs lot of practice =\r\nand effort, unless one is very very pure (internally), which is too rare in=\r\n this age..&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_1454937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_1454937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;IMO the l=\r\nine from the Aghora book should be taken as an attitude to be inculcated as=\r\n a method of sadhana. To develop surrender, and as we try we may find resis=\r\ntance - due to deep conditioned responses - which means we still have to ma=\r\nke conscious freewill choices and live by them, and also is an indication t=\r\nhat we may need to work on perfecting surrender. If surrender is truly perf=\r\nect, there is no need for anything. But then, as in all things in spiritual=\r\n life, none of it is easy, and we have to keep trying and trying..&lt;/div&gt;&lt;di=\r\nv id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_1454937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;=\r\nyui_3_16_0_1_1454937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;BTW one of the very typical s=\r\nadhanas is to imagine the form of the choosen deity in the heart and medita=\r\nte thus... if this practice is done daily, with patience, and sincerity, it=\r\n can, so people say, bring many benefits eventually.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_=\r\n16_0_1_1454937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_1=\r\n454937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Hope this helps.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0=\r\n_1_1454937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_14549=\r\n37201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;-Regards&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_145493720=\r\n1388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_1454937=\r\n201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0_1_14=\r\n54937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yui_3_16_0=\r\n_1_1454937201388_31994&quot; dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;y